The paper proposes a novel presentation data model for helping users construct join queries and navigate databases on a conceptual entity-relationship level. This involves interactive browsing and navigation, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (HCI) and user experience. The paper also deals with relational databases, which falls under the database (DB) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves querying tasks, which could fall under information retrieval (IR). The use of an enriched table and entity references could also suggest a focus on deep learning (DL) and natural language processing (NLP), falling under the sub-category of computational linguistics (CL).
